# Environment variables template.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (or `.env.<environment>.local`) and fill in real values.
# `.env*.local` files MUST NOT be committed — the repo's .gitignore enforces this.
# See docs/security/01-secrets.md for the full policy on secrets handling.
#
# This template repository has no runtime code, so no secrets are required here.
# When forking for a concrete project, replace this file with your project's
# actual environment contract (public config + comments pointing to where secrets
# are provisioned, e.g. "SECRET_KEY — from 1Password vault X" or
# "DATABASE_URL — see ops runbook at <link>").
#
# Keep this file free of real values; treat it as documentation.
